cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "QS Simulations: computational companions to the Quantum Social Physics framework"
message: "If you use this software, please cite both this repository and the QS framework paper."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Lee
    given-names: Kangwon
    email: kangwon.lee@ieee.org
    affiliation: "Tech University of Korea (TU Korea)"
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"   # TODO: confirm ORCID before the Zenodo DOI is minted
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/kwlee2025cpp/qs-simulations"
keywords:
  - agent-based modeling
  - social contagion
  - generalized reciprocity
  - quantum cognition
  - QQ equality
  - trust capital
  - AI safety
abstract: >-
  Neutral, shareable simulation companions to the Quantum Social Physics (QS) framework.
  Includes a severe-test agent-based model of generalized vs. direct reciprocity (P2.4),
  an asymmetric machine-node propagation model (P2.5), and a parameter-free QQ-equality
  model-recovery study plus a live question-order harness for the "society of LLMs"
  order-vs-count experiment (P3.2-M). Designed as severe tests that can refute the
  framework's predictions, not confirm them.
